What is an S3 Bucket

Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service) is an AWS service used to store and retrieve files over the internet.

A bucket is a container where files are stored in S3.

👉 In simple words:
S3 Bucket = Folder in the cloud used to store files.


What is Docker?

Docker is a containerization platform used to build, package, and run applications in containers.

Simple Definition

Docker is a tool that packages an application with all its dependencies into a container so it can run anywhere.
